  "texts": [
    "Autoencoders and Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) are also notable in the context of unsupervised feature learning and dimensionality reduction (Mahmud et al. 2021).",
    "Zhuang et al. (2024) employed non-invasive acoustic sensing to monitor gas composition in spent nuclear fuel canisters.",
    "Using ultrasonic transducers, they detected changes in gas mixtures with methods including the time-of-flight (TOF), differential, and autoencoder techniques.",
    "The TOF method successfully identified abnormal gas concentrations below 1.0%, while both the variational autoencoder (VAE) and Wasserstein autoencoder (WAE) effectively distinguished benchmark and abnormal states based on reconstruction errors.",
    "This method is particularly beneficial for datasets with limited labeled samples, as VAEs can leverage unlabeled data for pretraining."
